Tactical ML Proposal: Enhancing SAR Coverage in Niche Risk Scenarios

Objective

Improve coverage of low-volume but high-impact typologies‚Äîsuch as Human trafficking and Terrorist financing‚Äîby using a neighbour-based tactical machine learning approach. This method targets suspicious activity that sits below current operational thresholds but closely resembles known high-risk patterns.


---

Current Challenge

Detection relies on a fixed high threshold (e.g., score ‚â• 0.98), optimized for precision.

Low-prevalence typologies generate few SARs, limiting coverage.

High-risk customers with slightly lower scores remain unalerted.



---

Proposed Solution

1. Anchor on Known SARs:

Use high-scoring SARs from key typologies as reference points (‚Äúbeacons‚Äù).



2. Neighbourhood Search:

Identify customers whose model feature profiles are most similar to anchor SARs.

Focus on those scoring just below threshold (e.g., 0.85‚Äì0.98).



3. Risk Prioritisation:

Overlay similarity results with typology and segment metadata.

Rank customers by combined risk index.



4. Operational Triage:

Generate tactical lists for intelligence or investigations teams.

Integrate seamlessly with existing workflows.





---

Expected Impact

Today	With Tactical ML

Focused only on top threshold scores	Captures high-risk customers below threshold
Limited SAR coverage for niche typologies	Expanded SAR coverage in human trafficking, terrorist financing, etc.
Reactive detection	Intelligence-led, proactive targeting
Static thresholding	Adaptive, data-driven neighbourhood search



---

Success Metrics

